President Biden has declared a major disaster in Tennessee due to a severe winter storm that occurred from December 22 to December 27, 2022. Federal aid will be provided to supplement state and local recovery efforts in the affected areas. The federal funding will be available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. Brian F. Schiller has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations, and additional designations may be made in the future based on further damage assessments. For more information, the media can contact the FEMA News Desk.